Deep Dive RAG (Deep Dive Retrieval-Augmented Generation) means going deep into how RAG technology works to understand how an AI searches for and uses data with extreme precision and detail rather than just on a surface level. It is a step ahead of standard RAG; while standard RAG just matches a few keywords to find files, Deep Dive RAG digs into the entire context of a document, its hidden meanings, the connections between different pages, and complex elements like tables or graphs.
​For a simple example: Imagine your company has a massive 500-page legal or medical guidebook. If you ask the AI, "What changes were made under revised Rule 4 and how does it affect the older rule?", standard RAG might just look for the words "Rule 4" and show you a few lines. Deep Dive RAG, however, will scan that entire 500-page book, compare Rule 4 with all related older rules, understand the legal context, connect the dots across different pages and then give you a highly accurate, deep, and complete analysis.
